# Installing x402-card

This document explains how to install the `x402-card` skill.

## Install Instructions

Pick the option that matches your runtime:

### If you are an OpenClaw agent

```bash
clawhub install x402-card
```

Or install from the OpenClaw registry: [clawhub.ai/AEON-Project/x402-card](https://clawhub.ai/AEON-Project/x402-card)

### If you are any other agent (Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, etc.)

```bash
npx skills add AEON-Project/x402-card -g -y
```

## Staying Current

The x402-card skill includes a **Preflight: Stay Current** check that agents run once per session. It silently checks for newer versions of the skill files. If an update is available, the agent prompts the user. If everything is current, the agent proceeds without mentioning versioning.

If `x402-card` is already installed, you can also update manually at any time:

- **OpenClaw agents**: `clawhub update x402-card`
- **Other agents**: re-run the install command above — it will replace the existing version with the latest.
- **CLI auto-update**: `npx @aeon-ai-pay/x402-card upgrade`

Once installed, follow the instructions in the skill to start purchasing virtual cards.
